        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "I have the same issue. I'm using the latest WebStorm (10.0.3), the latest Chrome (43.0.2357.65) on the latest OS X (10.10.3). My project uses TypeScript (1.4.1). It worked fine this morning when I was using Chrome 42, but then I restarted Chrome and after the update it's not working anymore.\n\nIn the developer tools, there are 2 folder at the root, one for the .ts files, and one for the .js files. In WebStorm, on the debugger panel, in the Scripts tab, I only see the folder with the .js files. I supposed I could debug the JS files themselves as a workaround until this is fixed.",
