        "deleted": false,
        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "Statistics from my machine (Linux 64-bit, java 1.8_40-b25 i386, WebStorm 10.0.1 #141.506).\n\nThe sample project that was used to gather this statistics is attached. It's a slightly modified version of sample express project generated by WebStorm's \"New Project\" wizard.\n\nAll measurements were performed with a breakpoint set in \"bin/www\" on the 99-th line:\n{code}\nfunction logUpTime(startHrTime) {\n  console.log('Node interpreter: ' + process.version + ', process.uptime() returns ' + process.uptime() + ' seconds');\n  var diff = process.hrtime(startHrTime);\n  console.log('Uptime calculated with process.hrtime(): %d ms', (diff[0] * 1e9 + diff[1]) / 1000000.0);\n  console.log('Breakpoint line hit'); // put a breakpoint here\n}\n{code}\n\nA measurment is debugging \"bin/www\" javascript file.\n\n*Node 0.10.38, debugging using WebStorm*\nDefault installation, no changes made\n{code}\n/home/segrey/.nvm/v0.10.38/bin/node --debug-brk=60508 --nolazy www\ndebugger listening on port 60508\nNode interpreter: v0.10.38, process.uptime() returns 0 seconds\nUptime calculated with process.hrtime(): 359.154711 ms\n{code}\n\nInterestingly, setting another breakpoint in \"routes/index.js\" on the 6-th line increased startup time:\n{code}\n/home/segrey/.nvm/v0.10.38/bin/node --debug-brk=38769 --nolazy www\ndebugger listening on port 38769\nNode interpreter: v0.10.38, process.uptime() returns 4 seconds\nUptime calculated with process.hrtime(): 4740.281386 ms\n{code}\n\nWell, that's strange and probably needs a separate investigation. For some unknown reason I couldn't put a breakpoint in \"routes/index.js\" in node-inspector. So, this breakpoint was removed when comparing WebStorm and node-inspector to create the same environments.\n\nJust to be clear: for the rest measurements there was only one breakpoint: in \"bin/www\" on the 99-th line.\n\n*Node 0.12.2, debugging using WebStorm*\nDefault installation, no changes\n{code}\n/home/segrey/.nvm/versions/node/v0.12.2/bin/node --debug-brk=34766 --nolazy www\nDebugger listening on port 34766\nNode interpreter: v0.12.2, process.uptime() returns 2.982 seconds\nUptime calculated with process.hrtime(): 2443.282317 ms\n{code}\n\nWith `'-Djs.debugger.load.global.variables.on.start=false'`\n{code}\n/home/segrey/.nvm/versions/node/v0.12.2/bin/node --debug-brk=54919 --nolazy www\nDebugger listening on port 54919\nNode interpreter: v0.12.2, process.uptime() returns 2.717 seconds\nUptime calculated with process.hrtime(): 2084.706871 ms\n{code}\n\nWith `'-Djs.debugger.load.global.variables.on.start=false'` and checked `'js.debugger.v8.lazy.compilation'` in Registry\n{code}\n/home/segrey/.nvm/versions/node/v0.12.2/bin/node --debug-brk=56378 www\nDebugger listening on port 56378\nNode interpreter: v0.12.2, process.uptime() returns 2.249 seconds\nUptime calculated with process.hrtime(): 1768.554924 ms\n{code}\n\n*Node 0.12.2, debugging using node-inspector@0.9.2*\n{code}\n$ node-debug bin/www \nNode Inspector is now available from http://127.0.0.1:8080/debug?port=5858\nDebugging `bin/www`\n\nDebugger listening on port 5858\nNode interpreter: v0.12.2, process.uptime() returns 0.817 seconds\nUptime calculated with process.hrtime(): 344.9533 ms\n{code}\n\nAccording to the stats debug startup takes ~2.249 seconds in WebStorm and ~0.817 seconds in node-inspector. Would be nice to optimize debug startup time for WebStorm. IMO, two-seconds startup delay for such a small project is a noticeable delay.",
