        "parentId": null,
        "deleted": false,
        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "Totally agree. I also run against this occasion many times per day.\nI also should notice, that WebStorm's support of NodeJs modules is very, very poor. It does not understand, that exported class (Package in your example) is Package. Somewhere in code, when I require this module (\"var Package = require ...\") and write \"new Package\", it does not suggest constructor arguments, no intellisense for properties and methods, it can't detect inheritance between classes in different modules. Every time I ask myself: how do other people organize their code, how do they live without expected suggestions and error marks? And your example is, of course, one of the annoying.",
