        "name": "description",
        "value": "What steps will reproduce the problem?\n1. Enable and configure jscs as provided with screen1.png and use the following jscs configuration:\n{\n  \"excludeFiles\": [\"build/**\", \"node_modules/**\"],\n  \"esnext\": true,\n  \"esprima\": \"./node_modules/babel-jscs\",\n  \"verbose\": true,\n  \"preset\": \"airbnb\",\n  \"validateIndentation\": 4\n}\n\nWhat is the expected result?\n- jscs validation within webstorm\n\nWhat happens instead?\nError message \"JSCS; Cannot find module 'esprima-fb'\" - as can be seen in screen1.png at the top\n\nI've linked WEB-15087 as I think the \"esprima\" property seems to be hardcoded. But esprima-fb seems to be deprecated as stated here: https://github.com/facebook/esprima/issues/111\n\nInstalling esprima-fb as an dependency just for WebStorm jscs is currently a workaround but I think it might not be a usefull one.\n\nPossible solutions:\n1) use \"esprima\" setting as given from .jscsrc\n2) remove hardcoded \"esprima\" setting and offer a textfield configuration possibility to this property"
