    "comment": [{
        "id": "27-1012011",
        "author": "lena",
        "authorFullName": "Elena Pogorelova",
        "issueId": "WEB-16871",
        "parentId": null,
        "deleted": false,
        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "JSDoc itself doesn't yet provide support for ES6 destructured parameters. The suggested way to document them is \n{code}\n/**\n * @param {object} dummy\n * @param {number} dummy.foo\n * @param {number} dummy.bar\n * @return {number}\n */\nfunction main({foo, bar}) {\n    return foo + bar;\n}\n{code}\n(https://github.com/jsdoc3/jsdoc/issues/987)\n\nBut WebStorm doesn't support this either",
        "shownForIssueAuthor": false,
        "created": 1433937913010,
        "updated": 1433937927459,
        "permittedGroup": null,
        "replies": []
    }, {
        "id": "27-1012040",
        "author": "trikadin",
        "authorFullName": "Konstantin Kutsyllo",
        "issueId": "WEB-16871",
        "parentId": null,
        "deleted": false,
        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "I think it's have a sense to support a JSDoc style from my example -- because the guys from closure compiler's team chose this way:\n\nhttps://github.com/google/closure-compiler/issues/773",
        "shownForIssueAuthor": false,
        "created": 1433938631268,
        "updated": null,
        "permittedGroup": null,
        "replies": []
    }, {
        "id": "27-1014753",
        "author": "Serge_Zarouski",
        "authorFullName": "Serge Zarouski",
        "issueId": "WEB-16871",
        "parentId": null,
        "deleted": false,
        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "I would like to add that it would be great if WebStorm could also support destructured variables too:\n\n{code:lang=javascript}\n/**\n * @param {{getComponent: function, data: Object}} params\n */\nfunction fn(params) {\n\tvar {getComponent, data} = params;\n}\n{code}\n\ngetComponent should be a function and data should be an Object",
        "shownForIssueAuthor": false,
        "created": 1434424347885,
        "updated": null,
        "permittedGroup": null,
        "replies": []
    }],
    "tag": [{"value": "ES6", "cssClass": "tag0"}, {"value": "JSDoc", "cssClass": "tag0"}]
