        "jiraId": null,
        "text": "@peter I have the same issue.  Here's what I have been able to capture (a thread-dump so far):\n\n```\n-> % ~/bin/idea-IU-141.713.2/bin/idea.sh             \nPicked up JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS: -javaagent:/usr/share/java/jayatanaag.jar \nJava HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM warning: ignoring option MaxPermSize=350m; support was removed in 8.0\nPicked up _JAVA_OPTIONS: -Dawt.useSystemAAFontSettings=on\n[  11549]   WARN - om.intellij.util.ProfilingUtil - Profiling agent is not enabled. Add -agentlib:yjpagent to idea.vmoptions if necessary to profile IDEA. \n^C[ 551666]   WARN - api.vfs.impl.local.FileWatcher - Watcher terminated with exit code 130 \n```\n\nTrying to capture a CPU snapshot, but the IDE is unresponsive.  The menu at the top (the Unity menu) is actually Chrome's menu (the window behind IJ), not IntelliJ's menu.\n\n",
        "shownForIssueAuthor": false,
