        "text": "After posting about the issue on Ubuntu forums I also inquired in the Google group thread. Apparently I was not using strace to print the status of child PIDs, so the FUTEX_WAIT for the top-level thread may not have been the issue.\n\nUnfortunately, when I use strace with -F to get the child PID status, I no longer see the issue--IDEA finishes indexing the workspace, I don't see 100% load on one processor, and everything continues fine (until I abort strace, at which point the issue returns as soon as I try to do anything in the IDE).\n\nI let the process run until it crashed and am attaching the Java crash dump. At the time of crash, the error was:\n\n#  Internal Error (safepoint.cpp:310), pid=9169, tid=140214810965760\n#  guarantee(PageArmed == 0) failed: invariant\n\nIs this maybe a JNI problem?\n",
